* Zyber watched DeathSchythe relax as the salve took effect, she simply 
stepping back and walking back over to the fire.
Soon it would be time to hunt down their meal, one that would last a few 
days so that she could dwell on healing this injured bot.
Zyber sat crosslegged in front of the fire and looked at the flames 
reflection in the abmer surface of the tea.
This  Blaster, so he had told her his name, was going to take up most of her 
time and energy. But as long as he recovered it would be fine.
Zyber sighed and stretched out in front of the fire, knowing that it was 
going to be a long night.*
